    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-09-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-09-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1263"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1263">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.2311/55.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of New Mexico</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santa Fé, N. Mex.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-09-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 9, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Replying to your telegram. It will be entirely agreeable to the State of New
                    Mexico to have Mexican troops pass through our State under such regulations as
                    may be imposed by the United States Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William C. McDonald.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
